        <header>
            <h1>Human Avatar AI Interviewer</h1>
            <div class="meta-data">
                <span><span class="badge">v1.0</span></span>
                <span>Type: Product Scope Document</span>
                <span>Status: <strong>Approved</strong></span>
            </div>
        </header>

        <section id="summary">
            <h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
            <p>The Human Avatar AI Interviewer is a screening automation platform designed to conduct real-time, face-to-face video interviews. Its primary objective is to replace the time-consuming "First Round" phone or Zoom screen typically conducted by human recruiters.</p>
            <p>By utilizing hyper-realistic AI avatars, the system engages candidates in natural, two-way conversation, asking playbook-based questions, handling interruptions, and answering candidate queries about the company—delivering a standardized, unbiased, and 24/7 screening capability.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="value">
            <h2>2. Value Proposition</h2>
            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>For the Company:</strong> Scale your screening capacity infinitely. Replace hours of repetitive introductory calls with consistent, high-quality AI interviews that deliver instant transcripts and feedback.
            </div>
            <div class="info-box" style="background-color: #f0fdf4; border-left-color: #be185d;">
                <strong>For the Candidate:</strong> Interview on your schedule, not ours. A stress-free, unbiased interview experience that gives you the time and space to tell your story.
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="features">
            <h2>3. Detailed Feature Scope</h2>
            <p>This section maps functional requirements to specific benefits for Recruiters and Candidates.</p>

            <h3 id="human">A. The "Human" Experience</h3>
            <p class="scope-text">Features designed to make the AI feel like a colleague, not a calculator.</p>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">1. Realistic Avatars (9 Personas)</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-A1</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> 5 Female and 4 Male high-fidelity avatars (American/European).</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Brand Consistency." Choose a persona that best represents corporate image. Eliminates unconscious bias related to mood/fatigue.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Comfort." Interacting with a realistic face is less intimidating than a blank screen or text chatbot.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">2. Low Latency (< 2 Seconds)</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-A2</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> AI responds to voice inputs in under 2 seconds.</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Realism." High-speed processing ensures the interview feels like a genuine conversation.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Flow." The conversation moves naturally, reducing awkward pauses.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">3. Interruption Handling</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-A3</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> AI stops speaking and listens if the candidate interrupts.</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Soft Skill Assessment." Captures how candidates handle conversational flow and turn-taking.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Control." Allows candidates to interject naturally without breaking the system.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">4. Custom Avatar Creation</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-A4</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> Create a manual avatar using a single photo.</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Hyper-Personalization." Have the CEO "personally" screen every candidate.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Connection." Builds stronger immediate affinity with the company.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 id="conversation">B. Conversation Intelligence</h3>
            <p class="scope-text">Features that manage the logic and flow of the interview.</p>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">5. Playbook Creation (Dynamic)</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-B1</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> Scripts adapt based on uploaded resumes or run as a standard list.</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Standardization." Ensures strictly merit-based screening.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Relevance." Questions are tailored to actual experience.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">6. Silence Detection (>30s)</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-B2</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> AI detects silence and prompts the user ("Are you still there?").</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate" style="grid-column: span 2;">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Coaching." Helps nervous candidates who might freeze up, gently guiding them back into the flow.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-block">
                <div class="feature-header">
                    <span class="feature-title">7. Multi-Lingual Understanding</span>
                    <span class="feature-id">FEAT-B3</span>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Scope:</strong> Understands non-English inputs but always replies in English.</p>
                <div class="impact-grid">
                    <div class="impact-item impact-recruiter">
                        <span class="impact-label recruiter-label">Recruiter Benefit</span>
                        "Global Reach." Perfect for assessing non-native English speakers' proficiency.
                    </div>
                    <div class="impact-item impact-candidate">
                        <span class="impact-label candidate-label">Candidate Benefit</span>
                        "Safety Net." Lowers stress if they slip into their native tongue briefly.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

             <h3 id="workflow">C. Workflow & Operations</h3>
             <p class="scope-text">Features that handle the logistics of the meeting.</p>
 
             <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 20px; color: #4b5563;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
                    <strong>Company Knowledge Base:</strong> AI answers FAQs (culture, benefits) based on uploaded docs.
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
                    <strong>Meeting Rejoin:</strong> 3-minute window to resume if disconnected.
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
                    <strong>Post-Interview Output:</strong> Immediate generation of Video + Transcript + Feedback.
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">
                    <strong>Mobile Capability:</strong> Full interview functionality on mobile devices.
                </li>
             </ul>

        </section>

        <section id="technical">
            <h2>4. Technical Requirements</h2>
            <p>The following prerequisites are required to ensure user satisfaction (The "Ask").</p>
            
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Requirement</th>
                        <th>Rationale / Why it matters</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>English Language</strong></td>
                        <td>The AI operates in English; candidates must have conversational proficiency.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>No Background Noise</strong></td>
                        <td>"Quiet Environment Required" – Ensures the AI hears the candidate perfectly for accurate transcription.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Good Internet Speed</strong></td>
                        <td>"Video-First Experience" – Required for the realistic avatar to load and lip-sync correctly.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

